00:06:34.620 --> 00:06:35.920
&gt;&gt; David M. Rubenstein:So
the title, okay.

00:06:35.920 --> 00:06:37.220
&gt;&gt; J.D. Vance: Yeah.

00:06:37.220 --> 00:06:38.520
[ Applause ]

00:06:38.520 --> 00:06:42.150 position:56%
&gt;&gt; David M. Rubenstein:Now, the
title, very often authors don't come

00:06:42.150 --> 00:06:45.720
up with a title right away, and
was that your idea for the title,

00:06:45.720 --> 00:06:47.230
or where did it come from?

00:06:47.230 --> 00:06:48.590
&gt;&gt; J.D. Vance: It came
through a conversation

00:06:48.590 --> 00:06:51.810
with my agent, this woman, Tina.

00:06:51.810 --> 00:06:55.800
You know, I wanted the word
hillbilly to be in the book title.

00:06:55.800 --> 00:06:59.060
And the reason I wanted that
word to be in the title is

00:06:59.060 --> 00:07:03.060
because I thought it captured
both this sort of particular,

00:07:03.060 --> 00:07:05.920
kind of cultural sub-segment
that I was trying to write about.

00:07:05.920 --> 00:07:08.830
But I also thought that
it captured, obviously,

00:07:08.830 --> 00:07:12.350
this sort of interesting insider
outsider dynamic that existed

00:07:12.350 --> 00:07:15.820 position:56%
in my family, where my grandma would
say, you know, we're hillbillies,

00:07:15.820 --> 00:07:17.550
we're allowed to call
each other hillbillies,

00:07:17.550 --> 00:07:19.520
but if anybody else
calls you a hillbilly,

00:07:19.520 --> 00:07:21.300
then you have to punch
them in the nose.

00:07:21.300 --> 00:07:25.480
And so it was this sort
of interesting word,

00:07:25.480 --> 00:07:28.800
that it always had a really
textured meaning as I grew up,

00:07:28.800 --> 00:07:30.920
and so I wanted that
word to be in the title.

00:07:30.920 --> 00:07:33.210
Bet elegy was really
something that it really had

00:07:33.210 --> 00:07:34.960
to take awhile before I was one,

00:07:34.960 --> 00:07:37.870
comfortable with making
it Hillbilly Elegy,

00:07:37.870 --> 00:07:42.310
and I think that was Tina's idea to
actually pair Elegy with Hillbilly,

00:07:42.310 --> 00:07:44.490
and there were a couple
of reasons for that.

00:07:44.490 --> 00:07:46.990
&gt;&gt; David M. Rubenstein:So now that
